xt von Digitalität, Rassismus und Solidarität - die Möglichkeit, die Pandemie anders zu evaluieren.  afunded by Backlisttransformation EOSC Future  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCOVID-19 Pandemic, 2020-xInfluence. 0aCOVID-19 Pandemic, 2020-xSocial aspects. 0aFragility (Psychology) 0aSocial evolution. 4aAffekt. 4aCorona. 4aCovid-19. 4aDigitalität. 4aGender Studies. 4aGeschlecht. 4aKunst. 4aPandemie. 4aQueer Theory. 4aQueer. 4aRassismus. 4aSolidarität. 4aSoziale Ungleichheit. 4aVulnerabilität. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh  aAffect.  aArt.  aCorona.  aCovid-19.  aDigital Media.  aGender Studies.  aGender.  aPandemic.  aQueer Theory.  aQueer.  aRacism.  aSocial Inequality.  aSolidarity.  aVulnerability.1 aCastro Varela, María do Mar, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut2 aBacklisttransformation EOSC Futureefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2021z9783111025100oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839459386?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839459386zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839459386/original  a978-3-11-074335-7 DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb20